## 3. Brand Identity

> All design and development decisions on the Kidlat CivicLabs website must adhere to the visual identity guidelines below, sourced from the official Kidlat CivicLabs Brand Guidelines (2025).

### 3.1 Color Palette

| Name | Hex | Role | Usage |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Vivid Azure** | `#0071BC` | Main Color | 60% — dominant across all materials |
| **Dark Azure** | `#041C23` | Neutral | 30% — complements main color; use for dark backgrounds |
| **White** | `#FFFFFF` | Neutral | 30% — complements main color; use for light backgrounds |
| **Fresh Sky** | `#29ABE2` | Accent | 10% — use sparingly |
| **Jade Green** | `#39B54A` | Accent | 10% — use sparingly |

#### Tailwind CSS Custom Colors

Add these to `tailwind.config.js`:

```js
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        'vivid-azure': '#0071BC',
        'dark-azure': '#041C23',
        'fresh-sky': '#29ABE2',
        'jade-green': '#39B54A',
      },
    },
  },
};
```

#### CSS Variables

Add these to `src/app/globals.css`:

```css
:root {
  --color-primary: #0071BC;      /* Vivid Azure */
  --color-dark: #041C23;         /* Dark Azure */
  --color-white: #FFFFFF;        /* White */
  --color-accent-sky: #29ABE2;   /* Fresh Sky */
  --color-accent-green: #39B54A; /* Jade Green */
}
```

### 3.2 Gradients

Kidlat CivicLabs uses soft, abstract gradients as the main graphic element. Use them as backgrounds and visual accents — always whenever possible.

| Gradient | Colors | CSS |
|---|---|---|
| **Gradient 01** | Fresh Sky → Jade Green | `linear-gradient(135deg, #29ABE2, #39B54A)` |
| **Gradient 02** | Vivid Azure → Fresh Sky | `linear-gradient(135deg, #0071BC, #29ABE2)` |
| **Gradient 03** | Vivid Azure → Dark Azure | `linear-gradient(135deg, #0071BC, #041C23)` |

> ⚠️ **Avoid:** Combining any accent color with a neutral (e.g. Fresh Sky + White or Jade Green + Dark Azure).
>
> **Gradient Order Rule:** Accent → Main → Neutral. Order is reversible.

### 3.3 Typography

| Role | Typeface | Weight | Case | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Header** | Gibson | Bold | ALL CAPS ONLY | Tracking: 0, no italics |
| **Subheader / Body** | Systemia | Medium / Bold | ALL CAPS or Title Case | Use italics for emphasis |
| **Body / Footer** | Code Pro | Regular / Light | Sentence case | Tracking: 20, use thicker weight for emphasis |

#### Recommended Type Hierarchy

```
Primary:    Gibson Bold (Header) + Code Pro Regular (Body)
Secondary:  Systemia Medium (Header) + Code Pro Light (Body)
```

> **Note:** Gibson and Systemia are licensed fonts. Ensure your team has access via the Kidlat CivicLabs design resources (see Section 06 of the brand guidelines). As a web fallback, use `system-ui` or `Inter` if the custom fonts are not yet web-licensed.

### 3.4 Logo Usage

- **Primary (Horizontal):** Use whenever possible on light or dark backgrounds
- **Negative version:** White logo — use on dark backgrounds or over images
- **Positive version:** Colored logo — use on light backgrounds
- **Clearance:** Maintain spacing of one "K" unit horizontally and vertically around the logo

#### Logo Don'ts
- ❌ Do not squish or stretch the logo
- ❌ Do not rotate the logo
- ❌ Do not add strokes (subtle shadows are allowed)
- ❌ Do not apply foreign gradients or off-brand colors

### 3.5 Iconography

- Use **solid icons only** — no outline icons
- **Variant 1:** Apply brand gradients on icons to prevent a flat look
- **Variant 2:** Use neutral colors with accent color accents for a simpler look
- ❌ Avoid flat, single-color icons — they don't reflect brand visuals effectively

### 3.6 Graphic Elements

- **Gradients** — main graphic element, use always whenever possible; keep them soft and abstract
- **Patterns** — use when material lacks visual flavor, or to frame images/subjects
- Apply a **photo filter matching brand colors** when using photography

