## 9. Security

### Priority Matrix

| Priority | Measure |
|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical | API keys in `.env.local`, never in source code |
| 🔴 Critical | Zod validation on all API route inputs |
| 🔴 Critical | Rate limiting on contact form (Upstash) |
| 🟠 High | HTTP security headers in `next.config.js` |
| 🟠 High | Cloudflare Turnstile CAPTCHA on contact form |
| 🟡 Medium | CORS — only accept requests from `kidlatciviclabs.org` |
| 🟡 Medium | Resend domain verification (SPF, DKIM, DMARC) |
| 🟢 Ongoing | `npm audit` — run monthly |

### Security Headers — `next.config.js`

```js
const securityHeaders = [
  { key: "X-Frame-Options", value: "SAMEORIGIN" },
  { key: "X-Content-Type-Options", value: "nosniff" },
  { key: "Referrer-Policy", value: "strict-origin-when-cross-origin" },
  {
    key: "Content-Security-Policy",
    value: "default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline';",
  },
  {
    key: "Permissions-Policy",
    value: "camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()",
  },
  {
    key: "Strict-Transport-Security",
    value: "max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload",
  },
];

module.exports = {
  async headers() {
    return [{ source: "/(.*)", headers: securityHeaders }];
  },
};
```

### Resend Email Domain Setup

After verifying `kidlatciviclabs.org` in Resend's dashboard, add these DNS records at your registrar:

| Record Type | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **SPF** | Authorizes Resend to send email on behalf of your domain |
| **DKIM** | Cryptographically signs outgoing emails |
| **DMARC** | Instructs receiving servers on how to handle failed checks |

This ensures emails from `website@kidlatciviclabs.org` land in inboxes, not spam.

